# Accepted Trivy misconfiguration findings — each entry documents WHY the
# finding is by-design for this project. Review on every architecture change.
#
# Decision record: 2026-06-10 (PR-3 infra hardening). Security + FinOps lens:
# free hardening was applied (EBS root encryption AVD-AWS-0131, ALB
# drop_invalid_header_fields AVD-AWS-0052, non-root nginx DS-0002); the
# items below are either paid upgrades without threat-model benefit for a
# single-owner public-website account, or inherent to a public website.

# --- Encryption: SSE-S3 (AES256) is already enforced on every bucket. ---
# Upgrading to a customer-managed KMS key costs ~$1/month/key plus per-request
# KMS charges (CloudTrail writes continuously). A CMK adds key-rotation and
# cross-account audit controls that do not change the threat model of a
# single-owner account serving public static content. FinOps: rejected.
# S3 encryption should use Customer Managed Keys (tf-state, audit-logs, config, assets)
AVD-AWS-0132
# CloudTrail should use Customer managed keys to encrypt the logs
AVD-AWS-0015

# --- Public website topology: exposure is the product. ---
# Load balancer is exposed to the internet — it serves www.agevega.com.
# WAF + CloudFront sit in front; the ALB SG only admits CloudFront prefix-list traffic.
AVD-AWS-0053
# Instances in public subnets receive public IPs by default — this is the
# public tier of the 3-tier VPC (bastion + ALB nodes). Private and data tiers
# do not auto-assign public IPs.
AVD-AWS-0164

# --- Egress 0.0.0.0/0 on ports 80/443 only. ---
# Instances must reach ECR (image pulls), AL2023 repos (dnf), Let's Encrypt
# (DNS-01 cert issuance) and AWS APIs. Egress is already restricted to
# 80/443/22-in-VPC; destination IPs of those services are not enumerable.
AVD-AWS-0104

# --- Bastion SSH 22 from 0.0.0.0/0 (key-only auth). ---
# Workflow 01 deploys over SSH from GitHub-hosted runners whose IPs are
# dynamic. Password auth is disabled; access requires the EC2 keypair held in
# GitHub Secrets. BACKLOG: migrate deploys to SSM Run Command / Session
# Manager and close port 22 entirely, then remove this entry.
AVD-AWS-0107
